INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(51072, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You faced down those Thumpknuckles? Dat is worth a lot to us. Thank you.', 38556), -- WANTED: Prime Thumpknuckle
(60401, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, well, good job carting this one around, then. Hope they didn\'t give you any trouble.\n\nMaybe a little trouble would be acceptable.', 38134), -- Training in Ardenweald
(61884, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tubbins had better bring Gubbins along. He\'s the fun one!', 38134), -- Formal Refreshments
(61404, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mmm, water taste clean...\n\nLike me! I\'m cleanest!', 38134), -- Ember Court: Tubbins's Tea Party
(61882, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ancient rituals? This is my kind of party!', 38134), -- Formal Entertainment
(61407, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. The Accuser and I will personally lead the rituals during the Ember Court.\n\nWe will remind everyone of Revendreth\'s true purpose.', 38134), -- Ember Court: Atoning Rituals
(61706, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A new court in Revendreth? The Accuser must be pleased that you chose to include rituals of atonement in the festivities.', 38134), -- Ember Court: Entertainment
(61705, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You smart! Tubbins tea is best tea!', 38134), -- Ember Court: Refreshments
(61880, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If Kassir is coming, we had better ensure this is a formal affair.', 38134), -- Honored Attendance
(60236, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My most gracious gratitudes to you, Maw Walker!\n\n<Cryptkeeper puts the ring into his pocket and pats it comfortably.>\n\nNow I may attend the Ember Court in my finest appearance.\n\nI do hope the Accuser will be performing rituals there...', 38134), -- RSVP: Cryptkeeper Kassir
(61704, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The prince is wise to hold court. A timeless tradition of influence and prestige in this realm.', 38134), -- Ember Court: Guest RSVPs
(59661, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That went surprisingly well, all things considered. You and I have a real knack for this party-planning stuff.\n\nWe\'re ready to prepare our first real Ember Court!', 38134), -- Ember Court Rehearsal
(59660, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This court isn\'t going to throw itself. Let\'s get to work!', 38134), -- A New Court
(63065, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Come, come, my friend!\n\nIt is time... for a PARTY!', 38134), -- Sanctum Upgrade: The Ember Court
(63341, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see your skills in combat have improved even further. I trust you have made good use of our previous offer? \n\nZo\'dash is now instructed to offer the full suite of his services to you. I look forward to seeing their impact on your performance.', 38134), -- Sinfall Tactician
(60448, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Justice has been served.', 38134), -- Challenges in Revendreth
(60427, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Archon has sent word of your deeds, and agreed to support us in the battles to come. We will fix this broken cycle, with steps such as this leading the way.', 38134), -- A Call to Bastion
(60389, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ain\'t never been a friend to no Night Fae, but maybe it\'s about time we went lookin\' for more allies. Gotta start somewhere, I suppose.', 38134), -- Aiding Ardenweald
(60397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Maybe things get a bit more stable down there in Maldraxxus, now. Would do us all a lot o\' good.', 38134), -- Aiding Maldraxxus
(62263, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Must be nice to have the leisure to just sit and think all the time. \n\nI\'ve barely got time myself, with all the work I have keeping this place together!\n\nStill, that was nice of you to help out the old turtle.', 38134), -- Go Beyond!
(62459, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those are special moths! They really liven up the place, don\'t they?\n\nYou know moths work just as hard as anyone else, and they\'re under-appreciated. \n\nThanks for savin\' em.', 38134), -- Go Beyond!
(62447, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it! I cannot quite explain why that worked. Dreams can be strange, huh?', 38134), -- A Rare and Unusual Spirit
(62315, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve got a strange one today, $n.\n\nMarileth stopped by to say that his slime Plaguey is feeling more blue than usual, and asked if we could keep him entertained.\n\nWhat does this look like, a kennel? Plaguey can earn his keep like the rest of us! Get him out there, soldier!', 38134), -- Adventurer: Plaguey
(62467, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The branches of your expertise reach for the heavens and blossom. This is good.', 38134), -- Seed of a Thought
(61421, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'You have rescued both Enothia and myself. Allow me to repay your kindness and join you on your quest.', 38134), -- Champion: Blisswing
(59871, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nature holds as many secrets as it does gifts.', 38134), -- Catalyze This
(59999, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The forest sings in gratitude, Maw Walker. \n\nMy Queen is wise to place her faith in you.', 38134), -- Rebirth of the Grove
(60188, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was real nice of you. Not too many people take care of us old folks around here.$b$bShe even gave you silk! How nice. Here, why don\'t you take it? I certainly don\'t need it.', 37988), -- Go Beyond!
(62549, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It brings me joy to see more souls freed from that dark place.\n\nThank you Maw Walker, for continuing to help us.', 37988), -- No Wisp Left Behind
(60452, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did great! We learned a lot from your reports, and it sounds like you did some good down there. Good job!', 37988), -- Storm the Maw
(62400, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I remember those guys. Bad news. \n\nThey should stick to their own realm of existence!\n\nNice job cleaning house.', 37988), -- Go Beyond!
(36223, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have the notes. Let us see what they reveal about our enemy\'s strategy.', 37988), -- Leave Every Soldier Behind
(36209, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your search brought rewards?', 37988), -- What's Under There?
(36208, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Goren crystals are used by some as weapons. The acid left behind can be deadly though, even to the wielder.', 37988), -- The Crystal Shard
(36210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, yes, these shells will work perfectly.', 37988), -- Hard Shell
(36508, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for vouching for me, commander.', 37988), -- Is This One of Yours?
(35665, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, friend. I am in your debt.$b$bThis arrogant Iron Horde has made a dangerous enemy today.', 37988), -- We Have Company
(35883, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For years the ogres would make me fight, kill, and salute. My soul bled with each salute.$b$bBut because of you, I will never again have to salute an ogre.$b$bYou have helped me win my freedom, so I choose to use that freedom to serve your banner.$b$bToday, I salute you, commander.', 37988), -- The Fists of Vaandaam
(34704, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You do not have the look of a Stonemaul bounty hunter.$b$bWe escaped the clutches of their vile arena but at a heavy cost. We were forced to leave too many allies behind and too many ogres breathing.$b$bWe could use a fresh face, one that is unknown to the ogres.', 37988), -- A Rediscovered Legend
(35693, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have a true talent for combat.', 37988), -- A Harsh Reminder
(35664, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The ancients should not be a problem for your outpost for some time.', 37988), -- Seedbearers of Bad News
(35686, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These creatures are relentless in their assault against one another.', 37988), -- Rage and Wisdom
(49933, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you the new one? I\'m supposed to welcome you. Here, take this letter.\n\n<Blackguard lets out an exasperated sigh.>', 38134), -- For the Horde
(58122, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you the new one? I\'m supposed to welcome you.\n\n<Blackguard lets out an exasperated sigh.>', 38134), -- For the Horde
(53711, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 3000, 0, 0, 'Everyone in Boralus cheered when we saw the explosions up on that airship! The Horde will think twice before assaulting Boralus again.', 38134), -- A Sound Defense
(50599, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work!', 38134), -- Proudmoore Admiralty
(53052, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back, $n. Let\'s get to work.', 38134), -- Deeper Into Zandalar
(56031, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re just in time, $n. \nSpymaster Shaw was just informing me of some new intelligence we\'ve recently learned about the Horde fleet.', 38134), -- The Wolf's Offensive
(50071, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I love the tale of the Lightforged draenei. Dedicated to the Light and eradicating all evil!\n\nIt is important to remember they are no strangers to weakness. T\'paartos faced his weakness in order to ascend. \n\nWe must remember that we all have our flaws, but together we can overcome them.', 38134), -- For the Light!
(49266, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'T\'paartos is... enthusiastic. He means well, and he has a fire within him that few even among the Lightforged possess. Thank you for keeping him safe, $r.', 38134), -- Forge of Aeons
(49698, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, $n. You are about to bear witness to a ritual none but members of the Army of the Light have seen.', 38134), -- The Lightforged
(48962, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And so ends the tale of how the void elves joined the Alliance. \n\nTheir control over the void swung the odds in our favor in several battles.\n\nSome fear their use of the void, but I believe Umbric and Alleria have a unique perspective on things.\n\nThey are both aware of forces attempting to control and manipulate us. It\'s an important lesson for us all to remember. Are the decisions we make our own, or are they being twisted by an unseen hand?', 38134), -- Telogrus Rift
(49787, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Umbric\'s methods are a bit cavalier, but he seems competent. We must get to him before things become too dangerous.', 38134), -- The Ghostlands
(62054, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With these I\'m certain we\'ll catch the attention of Sire Denathrius.', 38134), -- Castle Nathria: Getting a Head
(59873, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And so a god is reborn by the hand of a mortal.\n\nThey greeted you with gratitude, yes? And perhaps surprise, as well.', 37988), -- Greeting a God
(59872, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your skills take root, Maw Walker.', 37988), -- How to Save a God
(59862, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your presence warms the grove.\n\nNow we learn, and grow.', 37988), -- A Savior for Lost Souls
(63046, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome. Together we shall thrive!', 37988), -- The End and the Beginning
(62624, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am so happy to see you have started to help restore the Queen\'s Conservatory to its former glory.', 37988), -- The Queen's Conservatory
(62285, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A most enlightening conflict. The Observer will be pleased.', 38556), -- Observing War
(62421, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The shape of the Gulper is now yours to call upon and use.', 38556), -- Gulper Soul
(47148, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even I didn\'t see that coming.', 38556), -- Something Different
(58936, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The balance is returning. Please accept this payment on behalf of myself and the other keepers of this place.', 38556), -- Beast Control
(57278, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have asked many others to collect heads as well! So even if none of these are the traitor\'s head, we shall find it eventually!', 38556), -- Bring Me Their Heads
(58163, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Partik quickly reads over the last few pages. His face turns pale.>', 38556), -- A Desperate Solution
(58162, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These masks must provide some clue to what\'s causing the possessions.', 38556), -- Mysterious Masks
(58164, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So few.... But each one is one more friend we can bring to bear against this madness!', 38556), -- Cult of Personality
(58161, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'No, no... what is happening!?', 38556), -- Forest Disappearances
(34072, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ugh, those smell awful! No, I don\'t need to see them. I\'ll take you at your word that you have them all.$b$bLet\'s get a move on before another Thunderlord patrol stumbles upon me.', 38556), -- Tar Get of Opportunity
(60640, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts revitalize the grove, and with it, countless spirits in need of aid.', 38556), -- Regrowth of the Grove
(62417, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nothing wrong with picking flowers for a living. It\'s good, honest work.\n\nAnd giving those blasted spriggans a kick in the rear is worthwhile too. Nice job.', 38556), -- Go Beyond!
(35702, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... Think of the orcs that will fall before us with this power...', 38556), -- Chains of Iron
(36081, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A gronn\'s eye is not something they part with alive. Your gladiator described a fight hard won and this trophy is a testament to your abilities.  Well done!', 38556), -- Proof of Strength: Gronn Eye
(36078, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A gladiator saw you tear this off the back of a gronnling, which I am sure did not part with it easily. It is more like a stone than a true scale though as these brutes are part stone it seems. Not an easy trophy to collect!', 38556), -- Proof of Strength: Gronnling Scale
(35137, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that we have the trainers, we can start training your forces to do something other than chop lumber. Heh heh.', 38556), -- The Sparring Arena
(36438, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have strong friends $p. We must make haste before the plants realize the way is open.', 38556), -- Beatface vs. Boulder
(47727, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the remnants of this seal, we can dispel the wards and enter my sanctum.', 38556), -- Tomb of Sargeras: Aegwynn's Path
(45383, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The power these fragments hold will allow me to call the talisman to us. Well done!', 38134), -- The Nighthold: Talisman of the Shal'dorei
(62442, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I find it helpful to have you do these things for me.', 38134), -- Aid the Covenant
(62465, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Always nice to lend a hand to someone who\'s just tryin\' to do their job. A metaphorical hand, obviously... although in your case, it\'s literal.\n\nI know what metaphorical means!\n\nAnyway, good work out there.', 38134), -- Go Beyond!
(49615, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very prompt. Now, I have need of your hands.', 38134), -- Trust of a King
(47514, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My father\'s trust is not easily earned.$b$bBelieve me.', 38134), -- Zuldazar
(37328, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. We have more immediate concerns to deal with until he visits.$B$BDark Ranger Velonara requires your immediate attention, $Gsir:maam;.', 38134), -- Not Here, Not Now
(37326, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, so you are the one your people spoke of so highly. We may discuss an alliance, but first...', 38134), -- Befriending the Locals
(35819, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Laughing Skull have always steered clear of that area because Khargax was very quick for such a huge beast. They will be pleased to know their eaten dead have been avenged.', 37988), -- Trophy of Glory: Khargax the Devourer
(35948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are impressed with your ability to slay the goren. They are relentless and voracious and can overwhelm those are not prepared.', 37988), -- Proof of Strength: Goren Tooth
(36080, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A gladiator saw you tear this off the back of a gronnling, which I am sure did not part with it easily. It is more like a stone than a true scale though as these brutes are part stone it seems. Not an easy trophy to collect!', 37988), -- Proof of Strength: Gronnling Scale
(59985, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to be back in Orgrimmar. \n\nI must report to the warchief, but I know what you can do in the meantime...', 37988), -- An End to Beginnings
(59984, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Victory for the Horde! It is time we returned to Orgrimmar as heroes and conquerors.', 37988), -- Dungeon: Darkmaul Citadel
(59979, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should weaken the ogres long enough for us to put an end to their plotting.', 37988), -- Like Ogres to the Slaughter
(59980, 6, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work! You didn\'t happen to save any of those explosives, did you?\n\n...I didn\'t think so. Oh well! I have plenty of other ways to blow up my enemies.', 37988), -- Catapult Destruction
(59981, 2, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for the aid, but saving me will not stop the ogres. \n\nThey already have enough life essence to complete the ritual!', 37988), -- Controlling their Stones
(59978, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There may just be a way that we can save Warlord Thunderwalker.', 37988), -- Right Beneath Their Eyes
(59975, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Darkmaul Citadel looms ahead. \n\nHerbert\'s proposed plan is... unconventional.', 37988), -- To Darkmaul Citadel
(60162, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t believe there is anything left to teach you, $n. \n\nNow you must go forth and find more beasts to tame and call your own.\n\nIf you ever need to store or retrieve your pets, speak with me or any other stable masters you encounter in your travels.', 37988), -- The Art of Taming
(59953, 6, 11, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I admit, I am rather ashamed I did not immediately recognize this beast.\n\nIt must be quite resilient if it was able to survive this long on its own!\n\nHere, let me teach you another trick. You\'ll want to have multiple pets to switch between if you\'re to be a hunter of any worth.', 37988), -- Hunting the Stalker
(59952, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With a little work, this can become an effective trap.\n\nPart of what makes a real hunter is the resourcefulness to use what your environment provides.', 37988), -- A Hunter's Trap
(61424, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Allow me and my saber to thrash your enemies once more!', 37899), -- Champion: Chalkyth
(60254, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have found only a few objects similar to this in all of our time here, that I am aware of. Whether it belonged to a race of creature or automatons that came before us, or they still exist somewhere, we do not know.\n\nThe metallic fragments of this piece appear similar in design to the walls that surround us here in Oribos, yet we have never seen something like this moving around in the city.\n\nI will add it to the cache of relics related to these mysteries. Take a suitable reward with you.', 37899); -- A Valuable Find: Tirna Scithe
